thread.title: Tesla Misses Model 3 Production Goal but Shows Progress

author: Tim Higgins
title: Tesla Misses Model 3 Production Goal but Shows Progress
text:
Tesla Inc. missed its goal of making 2,500 Model 3 sedans a week last quarter, though the auto maker showed progress toward building an all-electric car for the masses and said it doesnâ€™t require raising additional money this year outside of its standard credit lines.
The Silicon Valley auto maker said Tuesday it produced 2,020 Model 3 cars in the past seven days, an improvement from the 793 in the final seven days of last year. Tesla expects to make 2,000 more Model 3s in the next week.
